   <text>
      <body>
         <div type=”letter”>
            <opener><dateline><date when="1915-01-19">Mar. 23, 1915.</dateline></date>
               <salute>Dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Harriet</persName>:</salute></opener>
           <p>I am enclosing the advertisement for <title key="egoist" level="j">“The Egoist:</title> which <persName key="john_fletcher">Miss Weaver</persName> sent to me and asked me to forward you. She said you would understand, and it was all right.</p>
<p>By the way, I thought two of <persName key="ezra_pound">Ezra’s</persName> poems in your <title key="poetry" level="j">March number</title> particularly <title key="good" level="a">good: the young men riding horses and the chess game.</title></p> 
<p> As Spring comes around again I remember the pleasant visit I had from you last May. I wish you would come again, for I see no chance of my getting out to <placeName key="chicago">Chicago</placeName> again this Spring.</p>
            <closer>Afectionately yours,</closer>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
